Activities.Body:
Currently, the branchprotector will ignore repos that do not have
mandatory jobs, unless the repo has an explicit config.
This leads to orphaned required status contexts on GitHub if all jobs on
a repo are made optional.

This change will make the branchprotector always update the required
status contexts if there is at least one job, optional or not.

Note that this changes behavior that was deliberate (i.E. we tested for). I can not see any downside to this other than that it might cost us a bit more tokens. If there is any other downside I missed, please do tell :)

/cc @petr-muller @cjwagner

Activities.Body:
<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->

**What would you like to be added**:

sig-release maintains [`build`](https://testgrid.k8s.io/sig-release-master-blocking#build-master) and [`fast-build`](https://testgrid.k8s.io/sig-release-master-blocking#build-master-fast) jobs to periodically build and publish kubernetes artifacts. These jobs also update their respective [version markers](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-release/kubernetes-versions.md#ci). When other jobs run, they determine the version of Kubernetes to download by fetching the latest version marker for a particular version. Some of these jobs use the latest "fast" version and some use just the latest. In practice, the only time we need to use a non-fast version is when we are testing an os/arch combo other than `linux/amd64`, but there are a number of jobs that use non-fast version even though it is not required (example: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/96463#issuecomment-725478355).

**Why is this needed**:

Using a non-fast build is not necessarily wrong, but it does result in a stale build being used when a perfectly valid new one is available. We should always use fast-build when appropriate. However, it is difficult to enforce this as the version marker being used is not always surfaced in the prowjob config. In order to enforce usage of a particular version marker, jobs must utilize frameworks such as [kubetest](https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/tree/master/kubetest) where the version is selected in a standardized manner.

Work in this area is related to https://github.com/kubernetes/release/issues/1711 and https://github.com/kubernetes/community/pull/5014.

/cc @justaugustus @saschagrunert @kubernetes/release-engineering 
/assign

Activities.Body:
We currently do not allow code to merge directly to the client-go
repo (except the main `README.md`) since it's published by the
publishing-bot. The `CONTRIBUTING.md` file mentions this info as well:
https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md

To avoid accidental merges, we should explicitly
block PRs updates to non-README files by applying the
 `do-not-merge/blocked-paths` label.

Note that this is not an issue for other client-go repos since we
disable tide/automatic merging for those repos in the first place:
https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/blob/a2c4ac32a4bb360621d7d38278b5b065caa2f799/config/prow/config.yaml#L490-L521

The text for explanation matches the pull request template in client-go:
https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go/blob/master/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md

Slack thread for context - https://kubernetes.slack.com/archives/C0EG7JC6T/p1624349678194100?thread_ts=1624347242.192800&cid=C0EG7JC6T

Activities.Body:
<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->

**What would you like to be added**: For blunderbuss to only auto-assign to PRs once they are marked as mergeable.

**Why is this needed**: So PRs can be opened as WIP to allow showing what the PR would look like without actually bothering the eventual reviewers while the PR is being iteratively developed / tested.

It is a frequent pattern in kubernetes/kubernetes to open a WIP / do-not-merge PR to test something via the CI and get a linkable diff all in one, without the PR actually being intended for review yet. Often there is a comment explaining that the PR should not be reviewed.

It would be nice if we could just not assign people until after the PR is not a draft / WIP / "DO NOT MERGE".

/area prow
/area prow/hook
